	     <form action="/cgi-bin/mrate.pl" name="f106098602026551">
	     <tr><td id="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top"><a id="sj" href="/db/item.html?item=17722&amp;mid=106098602026551">RE: rng use?</a> <a id="fs8" href="/db/item.html?item=17722&amp;mid=106098602026551#post"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." width="17" height="11" /></a>
	     <br clear="all" /><small>Posted @ Fri, Aug 15th 6:29 PM 2003</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=162921"><span id=" ">Abajorsky</span></a><br /><span id="notbold">3 posts<br /><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [3.40]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p>One of the things people tend to forget is that a Warrior uses the Defensive discipline when tanking boss mobs.&nbsp;&nbsp;We get hit for 1/2 damage but we also only dish out 1/2 damage.  Half damage to the mob = much less agro than normal.  An aggro proccing weapon with a great ratio is a Warrior's dream when we go defensive disc.  At the high end of the game the single biggest factor that makes Warrior's the tank of choice for raids isn't AC/HP, its the Defensive disc.  Taking half damage for 3 minutes is like turning a 9k HP warrior into an 18k HP warrior.  The penalty is the reduced agro from the lower damage done by the warrior.  This is the main reason that agro proccing weaps should go to warriors first and foremost.....especially 2handers.  The amount of damage done by ripostes from raid mobs is incredible.  A 9k HP warrior can go down in ONE round of combat because of 3k hits + 3k ripostes.  Using a high damage, high delay 2 hander hugely reduces the amount of riposte damage the tank takes.  All the more reason this weapon should always go to a warrior first.<br/><br/>Bozack<br/>65 Warrior<br/>Xegony</p>&nbsp;<br /></td></tr>
